From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Neil Schemenauer <nas@arctrix.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 15:21:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] [native-helpers] Enable multithreading on the shared
 LinearLayout MLIRContext

linear_layout.cc keeps a process-wide MLIRContext built via the
ir.context() factory, which constructs it with Threading::DISABLED.
That setting forwards into every StorageUniquer on the context and
causes ParametricStorageUniquer::getOrCreate() to take the
getOrCreateUnsafe() branch, skipping the per-shard reader/writer
mutex. Every binding that calls StringAttr::get on this context
(identity_1d, strided_1d, zeros_1d, from_bases, apply) is then a
concurrent writer of an unlocked unordered_map under free-threaded
CPython.

Call enableMultithreading() on the context after construction. The
uniquer's own per-shard SmartRWMutex then synchronizes inserts and
lookups, with no extra process-wide lock needed.

Assisted-by: claude-opus-4.7
---
 python/src/linear_layout.cc | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/python/src/linear_layout.cc b/python/src/linear_layout.cc
index 21ad10125..b0b0b0b00 100644
--- a/python/src/linear_layout.cc
+++ b/python/src/linear_layout.cc
@@ -21,6 +21,11 @@ mlir::MLIRContext *getLinearLayoutContext() {
     py::module irMod = py::module::import("triton._C.libtriton.ir");
     // Keep the Python object alive for the life of the process without running
     // its destructor during interpreter shutdown (avoids segfaults).
     py::object ctx = irMod.attr("context")();
+    // The ir.context() factory constructs the MLIRContext with
+    // Threading::DISABLED, which disables locking inside its StorageUniquers.
+    // Re-enable multithreading so concurrent StringAttr::get calls from
+    // free-threaded Python are synchronized by the uniquer's own per-shard
+    // mutex.
+    py::cast<mlir::MLIRContext *>(ctx)->enableMultithreading();
     return ctx.release().ptr();
   }();
   return py::cast<mlir::MLIRContext *>(py::handle(ctxObject));
